Reasoning: The paper deals with the kinematic analysis of a family of 3R manipulators, which is a topic related to robotics and control. The paper discusses the workspace topology and singular curves, which are concepts commonly studied in the field of robotics. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also discusses the design parameters space and provides an explicit expression in the DH-parameters, which are topics related to mechanical engineering (cs.ME). The paper also discusses the necessary and sufficient condition for a manipulator to be cuspidal, which is a topic related to control systems (cs.SY). Other likely sub-categories include cs.ROB (Robotics and Vision) and cs.ROBO (Robotics and Automation).
